commitResults.messageTitle: Add seniors/caregivers with risk tags & auto caregiver IDs
commitResults.messageBody:
Logic / Commands
- Edit AddCaregiverCommand (add-cgr) to auto-assigns a caregiver ID (cN) at execute() time.
Model
- AddressBook now tracks a persistent caregiverSeq with getCaregiverSeq()/setCaregiverSeq(int)
- Model API: added String allocateCaregiverId(); implemented in ModelManager to call addressBook.nextCaregiverId().
Storage
- JsonAdaptedPerson now persists:
   - role discriminator: 'SENIOR' | 'CAREGIVER' | 'PERSON'
   - risk list for seniors (e.g., ['HR'])
   - caregiverId for caregivers (e.g., 'c10')
- Updated JsonAdaptedPersonTest to the new constructor shape and validations.
UI
- Edited PersonCard.java to render risk chips (tags) for Seniors (HR/MR/LR) and caregiver ID chip (cN) for Caregivers
- Darktheme.CSS: .chip-hr (red), .chip-mr (orange), .chip-lr (yellow) for HR MR LR

NOTE: REMOVED ALL EMAIL FUNCTIONS, CODES, AND CLASSES
